Overall SVI Score and 4 Themed Indicators Blog Page

Map Visualizations of Overall SVI Score and 4 Themed Indicators in CA Counties
Author

Jessica Li

Published

March 19, 2023

Modified

March 20, 2023

Overall SVI Score vs. Index Score for its 4 Themed Indicators in CA Counties

Since this map takes up a lot of memory, I decided to include the code for it and run the outputs on this separate file. Scroll all the way down to see the resulting map.

Code 
# First, import necessary library packages
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import folium
from folium.features import GeoJsonTooltip
Code 
# Next, import my dataset
svi_counties = pd.read_csv('California_COUNTY.csv')  # SVI variables and index scores for all California counties
Code 
# Filter for minority-related variables, SPL_THEMES, and RPL_THEMES (indicator category values and overall index scores)
scounties_min = svi_counties[['FIPS', 'COUNTY', 'E_MINRTY', 'M_MINRTY', 'EP_MINRTY', 'EPL_MINRTY', 'F_MINRTY', 'F_THEME3', 'SPL_THEME1', 'RPL_THEME1', 'SPL_THEME2', 'RPL_THEME2', 'SPL_THEME3', 'RPL_THEME3', 'SPL_THEME4', 'RPL_THEME4', 'SPL_THEMES', 'RPL_THEMES']]
Code 
# Filter for null values
scounties_min = scounties_min[(scounties_min['RPL_THEMES'] != -999)]
Code 
# Import geoJSONs to visualize the results on a folium map
counties_map = gpd.read_file('acs2021_5yr_ca_counties.json')
ERROR 1: PROJ: proj_create_from_database: Open of /opt/conda/share/proj failed
Code 
# first reformat geoid so that it corresponds to SVI data 
counties_map['FIPS'] = counties_map['geoid'].str[-5:]
counties_map.at[0, 'FIPS']  = '06'
counties_map['FIPS']=counties_map['FIPS'].astype(int)
Code 
# create merged file of geoJSON and SVI data
merged_counties_map = pd.merge(counties_map, scounties_min, on='FIPS')
Code 
# Create folium map centered in California
ca_counties_map = folium.Map(location=[37.5, -118], zoom_start=6,tiles=None, overlay=False)
Code 
# set color scale
custom_scale = (merged_counties_map['RPL_THEMES'].quantile((0,0.2,0.4,0.6,0.8,1))).tolist()
Code 
# define layers for folium map
fg1 = folium.FeatureGroup(name='Overall SVI Score', overlay=False).add_to(ca_counties_map)
fg2 = folium.FeatureGroup(name='Vulnerability Based On Socioeconomic Status',overlay=False).add_to(ca_counties_map)
fg3 = folium.FeatureGroup(name='Vulnerability Based On Household Characteristics',overlay=False).add_to(ca_counties_map)
fg4 = folium.FeatureGroup(name='Vulnerability Based on Racial & Ethnic Minority Status',overlay=False).add_to(ca_counties_map)
fg5 = folium.FeatureGroup(name='Vulnerability Based On Housing Type & Transportation',overlay=False).add_to(ca_counties_map)
Code 
# add to first layer overall SVI score
svi_score = folium.Choropleth(
            geo_data=merged_counties_map,
            data=merged_counties_map,
            columns=['FIPS', 'RPL_THEMES'],  # Get the county FIPS and plot the SVI index score (RPL_THEMES) for each county
            key_on='feature.properties.FIPS', # Get geo boundaries from FIPS column index
            threshold_scale=custom_scale, # Custom scale for legend
            fill_color='YlOrRd',
            nan_fill_color="White", # Use white if there is no data available for the county
            fill_opacity=0.7,
            line_opacity=0.2,
            legend_name='SVI Index Score', 
            highlight=True,
            overlay=False,
            line_color='black').geojson.add_to(fg1) 

# add tooltip
folium.features.GeoJson(
                    data=merged_counties_map,
                    name='2020 CDC SVI Scores Across California Counties',
                    smooth_factor=2,
                    style_function=lambda x: {'color':'black','fillColor':'transparent','weight':0.5},
                    tooltip=folium.features.GeoJsonTooltip(
                        fields=['COUNTY',
                                'RPL_THEMES',
                               ],
                        aliases=["County Name:",
                                 "Overall SVI Score:",
                                ], 
                        localize=True,
                        sticky=False,
                        labels=True,
                        style="""
                            background-color: #F0EFEF;
                            border: 2px solid black;
                            border-radius: 3px;
                            box-shadow: 3px;
                        """,
                        max_width=800,),
                            highlight_function=lambda x: {'weight':3,'fillColor':'grey'},
                        ).add_to(svi_score)  
<folium.features.GeoJson at 0x7f1f575c2f80>

After adding on all the map layers, I will add a legend to the overall map.

Code 
folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=merged_counties_map,
    data=merged_counties_map,
    columns=['FIPS', 'RPL_THEMES'],  
    key_on='feature.properties.FIPS', 
    threshold_scale=custom_scale,
    fill_color='YlOrRd',
    nan_fill_color="White", 
    fill_opacity=0.7,
    line_opacity=0.2,
    legend_name='SVI Index Score', 
    highlight=True,
    overlay=False,
    control=False,
    line_color='black').add_to(ca_counties_map)
<folium.features.Choropleth at 0x7f1f575c0160>

Totally just for aesthetic purposes, but I will add another overlay of the map in light and dark mode to provide a better background. Light mode does override dark mode, so it must be unchecked in order to view dark mode. Unchecking both options in the layers control will set the map to have no background.

Code 
folium.TileLayer('cartodbdark_matter',overlay=True,name="View in Dark Mode").add_to(ca_counties_map)
folium.TileLayer('cartodbpositron',overlay=True,name="View in Light Mode").add_to(ca_counties_map)
<folium.raster_layers.TileLayer at 0x7f1f575c0100>
Code 
folium.LayerControl(collapsed=False).add_to(ca_counties_map)
<folium.map.LayerControl at 0x7f1f503d4400>

Now that I added LayerControl, I can now generate my map!

Map of Overall SVI Score Compared to its 4 Indicators in CA Counties

Disclaimer: Theres a small bug with Folium where you cant access the tooltip for the first layer (Overall SVI Score) unless you click on another layer and click back on it!
